HEADWORD: Spica
<hw>Spi"ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Spicae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., an ear, as of
corn.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A kind of bandage
passing, by successive turns and crosses, from an extremity to the
trunk; -- so called from its resemblance to a spike of a
barley.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A star of the first magnitude
situated in the constellation Virgo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

